nequities around the globe. Bringing together leading thinkers and problem-solvers, this collection traverses the range of contexts at the frontiers of the field-from inadequate food supply and housing to unemployment and poverty. Editors Rodney Hopson and Fiona Cram demonstrate the effects of an engaged approach to evaluation, in which three considerations take center stage: its relevance, the relationships it engenders, and the responsibilities it requires. This is a handbook for tackling the social and economic problems of the twenty-first century which, though wicked, are amenable to the tools of the trade.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aEvaluation research (Social action programs). 0aSocial problems. 0aSocial servicexEvaluation. 4aEvaluation. 4acomplexity. 4aecologies. 4aglobal. 4apolicy. 4arelationships. 4arelevance. 4aresponsibilities. 4awicked problems. 7aEDUCATION / Evaluation & Assessment.2bisacsh1 aCram, Fiona, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHopson, Rodney, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360556540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503605565423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503605565.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles